oharis\n  | first = Athan (Editor)\n  | authorlink = Athan Theoharis\n  | title = Beyond the Hiss Case: The FBI, Congress, and the Cold War\n  | publisher = Temple University Press\n  | year = 1982\n  | isbn = 978-0-87722-241-5\n  | url = https://archive.org/details/beyondhisscaseth00theo\n  }}\n* {{Cite book\n | last=Weinstein\n | first= Allen\n | authorlink = Allen Weinstein\n | title=Perjury: The Hiss-Chambers Case\n | edition=2d rev.\n | publisher=Knopf\n | year=1997\n | ref=harv\n | isbn = 978-0-394-49546-0| title-link= Perjury: The Hiss-Chambers Case\n }}\n* {{Cite book\n  |author1=Weinstein, Allen  |author2=Vassiliev, Alexander\n  | title = The Haunted Wood: Soviet Espionage in America\u2014The Stalin Era\n  | publisher = Modern Library\n  | year = 1999\n  | isbn = 978-0-375-75536-1}}\n* {{Cite book\n  | last = White\n  | first = G. Edward\n  | title = Alger Hiss's Looking-Glass Wars: The Covert Life of a Soviet Spy\n  | publisher = Oxford University Press\n  | year = 2005\n  | isbn = 978-0-19-518255-2}}\n\n===Articles===\n* Kai Bird and Svetlana Chervonnaya, [http://www.theamericanscholar.org/the-mystery-of-ales-2/ \"The Mystery of Ales (expanded version)\",] ''The American Scholar'', Summer 2007.\n* John Erhman (2007), \"The Alger Hiss Case; A Half-Century of Controversy\", Center for the Study of Intelligence, [[Central Intelligence Agency]], 2007. Searchable by google: www.cia.gov \u203a ... \u203a Studies Archive Indexes \u203a Vol44No5 \u203a html\n* [http://www.britishpathe.com/record.php?id=69202 Interview footage with Alger Hiss]\n* Chervonnaya, Svetlana. [http://www.documentstalk.com/ ''Letting Documents Talk: A Non-Definitive History''.] Website about documents from formerly secret Soviet and other Eastern and Central European archives relating to the Hiss controversy.\n* {{Cite news\n  | title =Hiss: A New Book Finds Him Guilty as Charged\n  | work =Time\n  | volume =\n  | issue =\n  | date =March 29, 1976\n  | url =http://www.time.com/time/magazi