vin, David (1976). [https://web.archive.org/web/20091010185015/http://www.vqronline.org/articles/1976/winter/levin-court/ \"In the Court of Historical Criticism: Alger Hiss's Narrative\"], ''Virginia Quarterly Review Online'', Winter, 1976, 41pp.&ndash;71.\n* Levin, David (1978). [https://web.archive.org/web/20101228220532/http://www.vqronline.org/articles/1978/autumn/levin-perjury-history/ \"Perjury, History, and Unreliable Witnesses\"], ''Virginia Quarterly Review Online'', Autumn, 1978, pp.&nbsp;725\u201332.\n* {{cite web\n |last        = Linder\n |first       = Douglas\n |title       = The Alger Hiss Trials: An Account\n |work        = Famous Trials\n |publisher   = University Of Missouri-Kansas City School Of Law\n |year        = 2003\n |url         = http://www.law.umkc.edu/faculty/projects/ftrials/hiss/hiss.html\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20060830171725/http://www.law.umkc.edu/faculty/projects/ftrials/hiss/hiss.html\n |archivedate = August 30, 2006\n |df          = mdy-all\n}}\n*[http://hnn.us/articles/11579.html Lowenthal, David. (2005) \"Did Allen Weinstein Get the Hiss Story Wrong?\" History News Network]\n* {{cite web\n  | last = Lowenthal\n  | first = John\n  | title = Venona and Alger Hiss\n  | publisher = Intelligence and National Security\n  | date = Autumn 2000\n  | url =  http://homepages.nyu.edu/~th15/lowenthal.pdf\n  | accessdate = September 13, 2006 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20060909042031/http://homepages.nyu.edu/~th15/lowenthal.pdf| archivedate= September 9, 2006 | url-status= live}}\n* {{cite web\n |last         = Moynihan\n |first        = Daniel Patrick (Chairman)\n |authorlink   = Daniel Patrick Moynihan\n |year         = 1997\n |url          = http://www.access.gpo.gov/congress/commissions/secrecy/pdf/12hist1.pdf\n |title        = Report of the Commission On Protecting And Reducing Government Secrecy\n |publisher    = United States Government Printing Office\n |accessdate   = Septe