{"title_page": "Hitoshi Morishita (footballer, born 1972)", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name=Hitoshi Morishita<br/>\u68ee\u4e0b \u4ec1\u5fd7\n|image=\n|image_size=\n|caption=\n|fullname=Hitoshi Morishita\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1972|9|21}}\n|birth_place=[[Kainan, Wakayama|Kainan]], [[Wakayama Prefecture|Wakayama]], [[Japan]]\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n|height=1.73 m\n|position=[[Midfielder]]\n|currentclub=\n|clubnumber=\n|youthyears1=1988\u20131990|youthclubs1=[[Teikyo High School]]\n|youthyears2=1991\u20131994|youthclubs2=[[Juntendo University]]\n|years1=1995\u20132001|clubs1=[[Gamba Osaka]]|caps1=151|goals1=7\n|years2=2001\u20132003|clubs2=[[Hokkaido Consadole Sapporo|Consadole Sapporo]]|caps2=79|goals2=3\n|years3=2004\u20132005|clubs3=[[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]|caps3=9|goals3=0\n|totalcaps=239|totalgoals=10\n|nationalyears1=|nationalteam1=|nationalcaps1=|nationalgoals1=\n|manageryears1=2012\u20132013|managerclubs1=[[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]\n|manageryears2=2014|managerclubs2=[[Kyoto Sanga FC]] (caretaker)\n|manageryears3=2015|managerclubs3=[[Sagan Tosu]]\n|manageryears4=2017|managerclubs4=[[Thespakusatsu Gunma]]\n|manageryears5=2019\u2013|managerclubs5=[[Gamba Osaka U-23]]\n|medaltemplates=\n{{Medal|Team|[[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[Emperor's Cup]]|[[2004 Emperor's Cup|2004]]}}\n}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''Hitoshi Morishita'''|\u68ee\u4e0b \u4ec1\u5fd7|Morishita Hitoshi|born September 21, 1972}} is a former [[Japan]]ese [[Association football|football]] player and manager.\n\n==Playing career==\nMorishita was born in [[Kainan, Wakayama|Kainan]], [[Wakayama Prefecture|Wakayama]] on September 21, 1972. After graduating from [[Juntendo University]], he joined [[Gamba Osaka]] in 1995. He became a regular player from 1996. However his opportunity to play decreased in 2001 and he moved to [[Hokkaido Consadole Sapporo|Consadole Sapporo]] in July 2001. Although he played as regular player, the club was relegated to [[J2 League]] from 2003. In 2004, he moved to [[J\u00fabilo Iwata]], but he could hardly play in matches and he retired at the end of the 2005 season.\n\n==Coaching career==\nAfter retirement, Morishita started coaching at [[J\u00fabilo Iwata]] in 2006. He coached the youth team from 2006 to 2007 and the top team from 2008 to 2011. In 2012, he became the manager of the club, but due to bad club results, he was sacked in May 2013 when the club was at 17th place out of 18 clubs. In 2014, he signed with [[J2 League]] club [[Kyoto Sanga FC]] and became a coach. In June, manager [[Valdeir Vieira|Badu]] was sacked and Morishita managed the club in 2 matches as caretaker until the club signed with a new manager, [[Ryoichi Kawakatsu]]. In 2015, he moved to [[Sagan Tosu]] and managed the club for the season. In 2017, he signed with J2 club [[Thespakusatsu Gunma]]. However the club finished at the bottom place in 2017 and was relegated to [[J3 League]]. He resigned at the end of the 2017 season.<ref>[http://www.thespa.co.jp/thespa/club_newsinfo/news/newsdesc.cgi?newsid=2017110502 Thespakusatsu Gunma]{{in lang|ja}}</ref> In 2019, he signed with his old club [[Gamba Osaka]] and he became the manager for [[Gamba Osaka U-23]].<ref>[https://www.gamba-osaka.net/news/index/c/0/no/8965/ Gamba Osaka]{{in lang|ja}}</ref>\n\n==Club statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Continental\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Season !! Club !! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Japan\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Emperor's Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[J.League Cup|League Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[Asian Football Confederation|Asia]]\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n|[[1995 Gamba Osaka season|1995]]||rowspan=\"7\"|[[Gamba Osaka]]||rowspan=\"7\"|[[J1 League]]||13||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||14||0\n|-\n|[[1996 Gamba Osaka season|1996]]||28||2||4||1||13||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||45||3\n|-\n|[[1997 Gamba Osaka season|1997]]||29||2||1||0||5||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||35||2\n|-\n|[[1998 Gamba Osaka season|1998]]||27||1||1||0||4||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||32||2\n|-\n|[[1999 Gamba Osaka season|1999]]||23||0||2||0||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||28||0\n|-\n|[[2000 Gamba Osaka season|2000]]||26||2||3||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||30||2\n|-\n|[[2001 Gamba Osaka season|2001]]||5||0||0||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||7||0\n|-\n|[[2001 Consadole Sapporo season|2001]]||rowspan=\"3\"|[[Hokkaido Consadole Sapporo|Consadole Sapporo]]||rowspan=\"2\"|[[J1 League]]||13||0||1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||14||0\n|-\n|[[2002 Consadole Sapporo season|2002]]||29||2||1||0||6||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||36||2\n|-\n|[[2003 Consadole Sapporo season|2003]]||[[J2 League]]||37||1||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||40||1\n|-\n|[[2004 J\u00fabilo Iwata season|2004]]||rowspan=\"2\"|[[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]||rowspan=\"2\"|[[J1 League]]||9||0||0||0||4||0||3||0||16||0\n|-\n|[[2005 J\u00fabilo Iwata season|2005]]||0||0||0||0||0||0||2||0||2||0\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Career total\n!239||10||17||1||39||1||5||0||300||12\n|}\n\n==Managerial statistics==\nUpdate; ''December 31, 2018''<ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFIX07/?staff_id=3134 J.League Data Site]{{in lang|ja}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n!rowspan=\"2\"|From\n!rowspan=\"2\"|To\n!colspan=\"5\"|Record\n|-\n!G!!W!!D!!L!!Win %\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]\n|align=\"left\"|2012\n|align=\"left\"|2013\n{{WDL|44|14|10|20}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Kyoto Sanga FC]]\n|align=\"left\"|2014\n|align=\"left\"|2014\n{{WDL|2|1|1|0}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Sagan Tosu]]\n|align=\"left\"|2015\n|align=\"left\"|2015\n{{WDL|34|9|13|12}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Thespakusatsu Gunma]]\n|align=\"left\"|2017\n|align=\"left\"|2017\n{{WDL|42|5|5|32}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Gamba Osaka U-23]]\n|align=\"left\"|2019\n|align=\"left\"|''present''\n{{WDL||||}}\n|-\n!colspa