\n|nationalyears1=|nationalteam1=|nationalcaps1=|nationalgoals1=\n|manageryears1=2012\u20132013|managerclubs1=[[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]\n|manageryears2=2014|managerclubs2=[[Kyoto Sanga FC]] (caretaker)\n|manageryears3=2015|managerclubs3=[[Sagan Tosu]]\n|manageryears4=2017|managerclubs4=[[Thespakusatsu Gunma]]\n|manageryears5=2019\u2013|managerclubs5=[[Gamba Osaka U-23]]\n|medaltemplates=\n{{Medal|Team|[[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[Emperor's Cup]]|[[2004 Emperor's Cup|2004]]}}\n}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''Hitoshi Morishita'''|\u68ee\u4e0b \u4ec1\u5fd7|Morishita Hitoshi|born September 21, 1972}} is a former [[Japan]]ese [[Association football|football]] player and manager.\n\n==Playing career==\nMorishita was born in [[Kainan, Wakayama|Kainan]] on September 21, 1972. After graduating from [[Juntendo University]], he joined [[Gamba Osaka]] in 1995. He became a regular player from 1996. However his opportunity to play decreased in 2001 and he moved to [[Hokkaido Consadole Sapporo|Consadole Sapporo]] in July 2001. Although he played as regular player, the club was relegated to [[J2 League]] from 2003. In 2004, he moved to [[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]. However he could hardly play in the match and he retired end of 2005 season.\n\n==Coaching career==\nAfter retirement, Morishita started coaching career at [[J\u00fabilo Iwata]] in 2006. He coached youth team (2006\u201307) and top team (2008\u201311). In 2012, he became a manager. However the club results were bad in 2013 and he was sacked in May when the club was at 17th place of 18 clubs. In 2014, he signed with [[J2 League]] club [[Kyoto Sanga FC]] and became a coach. In June, manager [[Valdeir Vieira|Badu]] was sacked and Morishita managed the club in 2 matches as caretaker until the club signed with new manager [[Ryoichi Kawakatsu]]. In 2015, he moved to [[Sagan Tosu]] and managed the club in 1 season. In 2017, he signed with J2 club [[Thespakusatsu Gunma]]. However the club finished at the bottom place in 2017 and was relegated to [[J3 League]]. He also resigned end of 2017 season.<ref>[http://www.thespa.co.jp/thespa/club_newsinfo/news/newsdesc.cgi?newsid=2017110502 Thespakusatsu Gunma]{{in lang|ja}}</ref> In 2019, he signed with his old club [[Gamba Osaka]] and he became a manager for [[Gamba Osaka U-23]].<ref>[https://www.gamba-osaka.net/news/index/c/0/no/8965/ Gamba Osaka]{{in lang|ja}}</ref>\n\n==Club statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Continental\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Season !! Club !! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Japan\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Emperor's Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[J.League Cup|League Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[Asian Football Confederation|Asia]]\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n|[[1995 Gamba Osaka season|1995]]||rowspan=\"7\"|[[Gamba Osaka]]||rowspan=\"7\"|[[J1 League]]||13||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||14||0\n|-\n|[[1996 Gamba Osaka season|1996]]||28||2||4||1||13||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||45||3\n|-\n|[[1997 Gamba Osaka season|1997]]||29||2||1||0||5||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||35||2\n|-\n|[[1998 Gamba Osaka season|1998]]||27||1||1||0||4||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||32||2\n|-\n|[[1999 Gamba Osaka season|1999]]||23||0||2||0||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||28||0\n|-\n|[[2000 Gamba Osaka season|2000]]||26||2||3||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||30||2\n|-\n|[[2001 Gamba Osaka season|2001]]||5||0||0||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||7||0\n|-\n|[[2001 Consadole Sapporo season|2001]]||rowspan=\"3\"|[[Hokkaido Consadole Sapporo|Consadole Sapporo]]||rowspan=\"2\"|[[J1 League]]||13||0||1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||14||0\n|-\n|[[2002 Consadole Sapporo season|2002]]||29||2||1||0||6||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||36||2\n|-\n|[[2003 Consadole Sapporo season|2003]]||[[J2 League]]||37||1||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||40||1\n|-\n|[[2004 J\u00fabilo Iwata season|2004]]||rowspan=